(2) The gods dwell outside the world ,· its matter is too coarse and dense for their subtle nature. And they did not make the world, —for what motive could have led them, ever blesscd in repon, to trouble themselves with creating ,2 or what hurt had it been if we had not been born ? or whence could they have drawn the idea of man to make him ?
